Reasoning: The paper discusses methods for learning disentangled representations in the domains of graphics and computation, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on representation learning, which is a fundamental aspect of machine learning. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses methods for inferring generating parameters of images and rerendering them under novel conditions. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses models that can factorize a multitask learning problem into subtasks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of distributed representations generated by neural networks and proposes methods for improving them. Finally, cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper discusses methods for inferring generating parameters of images and rerendering them under novel conditions.
